  */}

  <hr class="section-rule" />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="column-wide">
      <p>
        Most people aren't financially unintelligent. They're
        financially underserved.
      </p>

      <p>
        The financial industry has spent decades making money sound
        complicated, partly because complication justifies fees. Most
        household money decisions are simpler than they look once
        someone calmly explains them.
      </p>

      <p>
        You don't have to wait until you've "fixed everything" to ask
        for help. Wherever you're starting is where we start.
      </p>

      <p class="pull-quote">
        Permission matters. To spend on what you love. To wash a
        ziplock bag if it lets you fly first class once a year. To
        want what you want and plan for it in plain English.
      </p>

      <p>
        Calmness is the most underrated financial skill there is. You
        can do this. You don't need to panic.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="audience-heading">
    <div class="column-wide">
      <h2 id="audience-heading">Who Stacey works with</h2>

      <p>
        Stacey works mostly with women navigating a transition.
        Retirement. Divorce. Widowhood. A late start. Caring for
        aging parents while raising kids. A divorce that left more
        questions than answers. An inheritance that arrived
        unexpectedly. A new career or a country move.
      </p>

      <p>
        Most are women who have been smart and capable in every
        other part of their lives, but have never had someone sit
        down with them about money without an agenda.
      </p>

      <p>
        You don't need to have it figured out before you arrive
        &mdash; no spreadsheet, no documents the first time.
      </p>

      <p style="margin-top: 1.75rem;">
        <a href="/services" class="cta">See how Stacey works</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
